description:
In this episode of ANN Profiles, Alyssa Truman interviews Hensley Moorooven,  the Undersecretary of the Seventh-day Adventist Church, about his life journey and ministry. From his childhood in Mauritius to his current position in the leadership of the Seventh-day Adventist Church, Hensley shares how faith, humility, and dedication to mission have shaped his life and career.
________________
